wikipedia_page.main: Cyril Woolford (c. fourth ¼ 1927 – 30 November 2018) was an English professional rugby league footballer who played in the 1940s, 1950s and 1960s. He played at representative level for Yorkshire, and at club level for Castleford (Heritage № 313), Doncaster (Heritage № 52), and Featherstone Rovers (Heritage № 370) (vice-captain), as a wing, or centre, i.e. number 2 or 5, or, 3 or 4, he was a committee member at Featherstone Rovers for a number of years.
